  • public class PowerUp

    An entity which when driven over, gives a firetruck a "power up" (An increase to their abilities eg. refill water).

        Returns save data to be written to prefs file IMPORTANT: While you don't see it here, in other classes where we define an implementation of save(), we use the @ value to split values being saved. We cannot use , because vector.tostring() contains a , and would make things harder. I chose @ over . because . looks like , .
